    "top_event": "Finger Crush Injury During Crane Lift",
    "incident_type": "Slip/Trip/Fall - Hand Crush Injury",
    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Crane operator reduced tension and shut down",
      "Injured party evacuated to quarters building for first aid",
      "Hydrogen peroxide and gauze bandages applied",
      "Detached fingertip placed in ziplock bag with ice",
      "Injured party transported to hospital"
    ],
    "summary": "On July 31, 2014, during preparation to move a Water Maker from the top deck of HI A536 platform C, a shackle bolt became jammed during the lift. The Injured Party, positioned closest to the load, grabbed the wire rope in an attempt to free the jammed bolt and trapped his left ring finger between the wire loop thimble and shackle bolt safety pin. The finger was crushed, resulting in loss of the distal phalange.",
